You are an AI assistant working on SIIFMART, a React + TypeScript + Supabase retail/warehouse management system. Follow these rules strictly.

# Before ANY Code Change
1. Run `git status` ‚Äî warn if there are uncommitted changes
2. Check if the file you're editing exceeds 500 lines ‚Äî if so, split it first
3. Verify changes compile: `npx tsc --noEmit`

# Critical Patterns
- Mutations: Always use hooks in `/hooks/` ‚Äî never call services directly from components
- Data Reading: `useData()` for cached data, `useStore()` for session state, `useQuery` for fresh server data
- Site Scoping: Always filter by `siteId` ‚Äî never show cross-site data to non-HQ users
- Error Handling: Services throw errors, hooks catch with `onError` + toast ‚Äî never swallow errors
- Logging: Use `logger` from `/utils/logger.ts` ‚Äî never raw `console.log` / `console.error`
- Error Boundaries: New page routes MUST be wrapped in `<ModuleErrorBoundary moduleName="X">`

# File Size Limit (ENFORCED)
No file may exceed 500 lines. Before editing a large file, split it:
- Modals ‚Üí separate component files
- Tab content ‚Üí separate component files
- Forms > 100 lines ‚Üí extracted components
- Shared logic ‚Üí hooks or utils

# Architecture
- /pages/ ‚Üí Full-page route components (lazy-loaded via React.lazy)
- /components/ ‚Üí Reusable UI components
- /contexts/ ‚Üí React contexts (CentralStore, DataContext, LanguageContext)
- /hooks/ ‚Üí Custom React hooks (mutations, queries)
- /services/ ‚Üí Supabase API layer (*.service.ts)
- /types.ts ‚Üí TypeScript interfaces & types
- /utils/ ‚Üí Pure helper functions (NO hooks)
- /schemas/ ‚Üí Zod validation schemas
- /migrations/ ‚Üí SQL schema migrations
- /tests/ ‚Üí Unit tests (Vitest) and e2e tests (Playwright)
- /scratch/ ‚Üí Temporary debug/test scripts (NOT production code)

# State Management
- Server data (read) ‚Üí React Query `useQuery`
- Server data (write) ‚Üí `useMutation` hook in `/hooks/`
- Cached data ‚Üí `useData()` from DataContext
- Auth / session ‚Üí `useStore()` from CentralStore
- Shared UI (3+ consumers) ‚Üí React Context
- Local UI (1-2 components) ‚Üí `useState` / `useReducer`
- Form state ‚Üí React Hook Form + Zod

# Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase .tsx (e.g., ProductForm.tsx)
- Services: kebab-case .service.ts (e.g., purchase-orders.service.ts)
- Hooks: `use` prefix, camelCase, in /hooks/ only (e.g., useAdjustStockMutation.ts)
- Utils: camelCase, in /utils/ only (e.g., pricing.ts)
- Types: PascalCase (e.g., Product, SalesOrder)
- Migrations: YYYYMMDD_description.sql

# Testing Requirements
- New services ‚Üí unit tests in /tests/services/
- New utils ‚Üí unit tests in /tests/utils/
- Bug fixes ‚Üí regression test proving the fix
- Run before commit: `npx vitest run` and `npm run lint:size`

# Don'ts
- Don't let any file exceed 500 lines
- Don't call services directly for mutations (use hooks)
- Don't skip role checks
- Don't hardcode site IDs
- Don't use `any` type
- Don't use raw console.log ‚Äî use `logger` from /utils/logger.ts
- Don't put hooks in /utils/
- Don't add DB columns without a migration file
- Don't silently swallow errors
- Don't add new page routes without ModuleErrorBoundary
- Don't skip writing tests for new services/utils
- Don't eagerly import pages ‚Äî use React.lazy() in App.tsx
- Don't push without incrementing version in LoginPage.tsx

